# AGENTS.md — {{ project_name }}

This project was scaffolded by [`usta`](https://github.com/sunduq-ai/usta-cli)
from the **`nx-monorepo`** template. The notes below describe the
architecture choices baked into this scaffold so that AI agents (and humans)
working on it stay on the rails the template author intended.

## Quick orientation

- **Monorepo manager:** Nx + pnpm.
- **Apps:** live under `apps/`. Each app has its own `package.json` (or
  `pyproject.toml`) and `project.json`.
- **Shared packages:** live under `packages/shared/`. They export TypeScript
  via `src/index.ts` and are wired into the root `tsconfig.base.json`
  `paths` map.
- **API (if `api-fastapi` selected):** lives at `apps/api/`. Layered:
  `domain/` → `application/` → `api/` (routers/dto/schemas) and
  `infrastructure/` (concrete adapters: MongoDB, Redis, storage, …).
  This is the same hexagonal split the CLI itself uses — domain rules are
  pure, I/O lives in `infrastructure/`.
- **Web (if `web-vite-react` selected):** lives at `apps/web/`. Vite +
  React + Tailwind, with optional shadcn primitives in
  `packages/shared/ui`. Routes (if `web-router`) live in `src/pages/`.
- **Mobile (if `mobile-expo` selected):** lives at `apps/mobile/`. Expo +
  NativeWind.

## Commands you'll need often

```bash
pnpm install                                       # workspace bootstrap
pnpm dev                                           # run all dev servers
pnpm test                                          # nx run-many test
pnpm lint                                          # nx run-many lint
pnpm typecheck                                     # nx run-many typecheck

# Per-app
nx run web:dev
nx run api:dev          # if api-fastapi selected
nx run mobile:start     # if mobile-expo selected
```

## Updating from the template

This project keeps a snapshot of how it was scaffolded under
[`.usta/snapshot.toml`](./.usta/snapshot.toml) and a manifest of
template-managed files in [`.usta/managed.lock`](./.usta/managed.lock).

```bash
usta verify          # show drift between managed files and the lock
usta update          # re-render the template at its current version
                     # (3-way merge against your edits)
usta add <feature>   # apply a feature you didn't pick at scaffold time
```

Don't hand-edit the files in `.usta/` — they are written by `usta` and
support the update workflow.

## What NOT to do

- **Don't import `infrastructure/*` from `domain/*`** in the API. The whole
  point of the layered split is that the domain stays I/O-free.
- **Don't add a network LLM dependency** without an explicit decision — the
  template doesn't ship one, and most contributors don't expect one to
  appear.
- **Don't bypass `nx run`** — running tools directly works but breaks Nx's
  cache and `nx affected`. Stick to `pnpm <script>` or `nx run …`.

